comments.body:
The core problem is that Conmon is attached only to PID 1 of the container. In a container with a PID namespace, that's perfectly acceptable as PID 1 in a PID namespace dying, causes the kernel to kill every other process in the namespace; since there is no longer a PID namespace, we no longer have that guarantee.

I suppose we could change Podman's state transition code for stopped -> exited (unmount the container, tear down the network) to also do a `crun kill --all` on the container to ensure all processes are gone. Alternatively, we could add a check of sorts to Conmon to check if there are remaining processes in the cgroup, and possibly kill them, when PID 1 exits?

@giuseppe @haircommander @rhatdan Thoughts?
